OL,3,CBurnham thanks Glasgow for 'stepping
OL,4,Cup to save' Commonwealth Games
OL,6,FPrime Minister Andy Burnham has
OL,7,Fthanked Glasgow after the city
OL,8,F"stepped up to save the Commonwealth
OL,9,FGames" when the future of the event
OL,10,Flooked in doubt.
OL,12,FThe Prime Minister wished athletes
OL,13,Ffrom the England, Scotland, Wales and
OL,14,FNorthern Ireland "good luck" for the
OL,15,Fcontest.
OL,17,FHe spoke after watching the opening
OL,18,Fceremony for the sporting contest at
OL,19,FGlasgow's Hydro venue on Thursday
OL,20,Fnight.
