OL,3,CBurnham thanks Glasgow for 'stepping
OL,4,Cup to save' Commonwealth Games
OL,6,FReferring to the Scottish runner who
OL,7,Frecently set a new world record, he
OL,8,Fadded: "I'm a keen runner but I don't
OL,9,Ffancy my chances against Josh Kerr's
OL,10,Fone-mile world record."
OL,12,FBut the Prime Minister also stressed
OL,13,Fthe importance of sport to communities
OL,14,Facross the UK.
OL,16,FMr Burnham said: "We're a country mad
OL,17,Fabout sport, so let's have more of it,
OL,18,Fin every part of the UK.
OL,26,@pD@HOUrD@WO]xD@ROU
